{"questionId":"9068927","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>White phosphorus is an allotrope of phosphorus and exists as P<sub>4</sub>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An equilibrium exists between PCl<sub>3</sub> and PCl<sub>5</sub>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">PCl<sub>3 </sub>(g) + Cl<sub>2 </sub>(g) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> PCl<sub>5 </sub>(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the equilibrium constant expression,<em> K</em><sub>c</sub>, for this reaction.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<em>K</em><sub>c</sub> =»&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mfrac><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msub><mi>PCl</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></mfenced><mrow><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msub><mi>PCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfenced><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math> ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068927","referenceCode":"21N.2.sl.TZ0.3c(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the equilibrium constant expression, Kc, for this reaction.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium","7.1 Equilibrium","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}